        "text": "照樣，　神定意向那些承受應許的人，更清楚地表明他的旨意是不更改的，就用起誓作保證。"
      },
      "cunp": {
        "version_id": "CUNP",
        "version_name": "和合本新標點（神版）",
        "lang": "cht",
        "text": "照樣，神願意為那承受應許的人格外顯明他的旨意是不更改的，就起誓為證。"
      },
      "nasb": {
        "version_id": "NASB",
        "version_name": "New American Standard Bible",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "In the same way God, desiring even more to show to the heirs of the promise the unchangeableness of His purpose, interposed with an oath,"
      },
      "niv": {
        "version_id": "NIV",
        "version_name": "New International Version",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "Because God wanted to make the unchanging nature of his purpose very clear to the heirs of what was promised, he confirmed it with an oath."
      },
      "nlt": {
        "version_id": "NLT",
        "version_name": "New Living Translation",
        "lang": "en",
        "text": "God also bound himself with an oath, so that those who received the promise could be perfectly sure that he would never change his mind."
      }
    },
